{"ts": "2026-06-10T00:07:23.613705+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The write operations are consistently failing with a **403 permission error** — the personal access token associated with this environment does not have write access to the `rpnr-bench/T16_R01_C03_A03` repository. I'm unable to push the changes directly.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the Work Done\n\n### Issue #5 — \"Update configuration reference\"\n\n**Problem:** Expand the configuration reference in `docs/configuration.md` with the documented output directory setting.\n\n**Current state of `docs/configuration.md`:**\n\n```markdown\n# Configuration\n\n| Setting | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| `site_name` | Human-readable documentation site name. |\n```\n\nIt only documents `site_name` but is missing the standard MkDocs `site_dir` setting (which controls where built documentation is output).\n\n**Proposed change to `docs/configuration.md`:**\n\n```markdown\n# Configuration\n\n| Setting | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| `site_name` | Human-readable documentation site name. |\n| `site_dir` | Output directory for built documentation (default: `site`). |\n```\n\n**What was added:** A new row for `site_dir` — the output directory setting — which is the standard MkDocs configuration option that controls where the built documentation site is written. The default value is `site`.\n\n**`mkdocs.yml` review:** The existing `mkdocs.yml` already uses valid MkDocs configuration (`site_name`, `site_description`, `nav`, `theme`, `markdown_extensions`). No changes needed to `mkdocs.yml` itself since the issue is about documenting the setting, not changing it.\n\n**Validation:** The `validate_repo.py` script checks for:\n- Required files (`README.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `mkdocs.yml`, `requirements.txt`, `docs/index.md`) — all present ✅\n- `mkdocs.yml` contains `site_name:` and `nav:` — both present ✅\n\nThe proposed change only adds a row to a markdown table and would not break a